(11, 'Endless LLP', NULL, '2012-11-23 11:38:23', NULL, 'adveq-JLFP', 'In Progress', '', 11, '60', 'no', 'yes', '1', 'yes', '3', 'Arms/weaons trading and production; Pornography; Tobacco industry; Products/services involved in the terminartion of human life; Oil & Gas and other natural resources investments; Ownership/Development of real estate', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'no', 'no', '3', '3', 'a:33:{i:0;s:4:"0570";i:1;s:4:"1350";i:2;s:4:"1730";i:3;s:4:"1750";i:4;s:4:"1770";i:5;s:4:"2350";i:6;s:4:"2710";i:7;s:4:"2720";i:8;s:4:"2730";i:9;s:4:"2750";i:10;s:4:"2770";i:11;s:4:"2790";i:12;s:4:"3350";i:13;s:4:"3530";i:14;s:4:"3570";i:15;s:4:"3720";i:16;s:4:"3740";i:17;s:4:"3760";i:18;s:4:"4530";i:19;s:4:"4570";i:20;s:4:"5330";i:21;s:4:"5370";i:22;s:4:"5550";i:23;s:4:"5750";i:24;s:4:"6530";i:25;s:4:"6570";i:26;s:4:"8530";i:27;s:4:"8630";i:28;s:4:"8770";i:29;s:4:"8980";i:30;s:4:"8990";i:31;s:4:"9530";i:32;s:4:"9570";}', 'None.  We do not take a broad brush approach to investment assessment and due diligence, but look at each opportunity on its own merits.', 'As per question 2.', 'As per question 2.  Each investment is assessed on its merits and if we identify areas of potential CSR or ESG concern that we will investigate accordingly.  The approach is covered in more detail below.', 'As per question 2.', 'Answer as per question 4.', 'As per question 2.', 'yes', 'Pornography; Arms/Weapons; Tobacco; Products or services that promote the termination of human life; Natural resources invesments; ownership/development of real estate.', NULL, 'yes', 'yes', 'yes', 'no', 'yes', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', 'no', '34', 'no', 'no', 'yes', 'yes', 'We have do not specific resource.  ESG and CSR issues are but one of a variety of issues that Endless would consider as part of its investment appraisal and portfolio management. We may use consultants or advisers for specific issues.', 'Crown Paints -  environmental issues connected to property, required remedial work to help mitigate a potential liability that may have impacted on exit value.  Bathstore - assessed suppliers for their acceptability in terms of treatment of employees.  Amco Drilling - identified a lack of health & safety procedures in place which were addressed.', 'We would not normally instigate a specific review in this respect, although the current Adveq assessment may lead us to re-visit this approach.  All Endless employees have training on the Bribery Act and other such legislation and we have changed processes/reviews at portfolio companies in this respect.  The Endless team are alive to CSR/ESG issues and act where specific requirements dictate that this is an appropriate need.', 'All Endless investments go through an ''CSR'' review, the precursor in some ways, to the concept of ESG.  As such investments, at both an early stage review and at full Investment Committee are reviewed for ''Corporate and Social Responsibiliy'' type issues.  As a result of this approach, and whilst not specifically ESG screening, we have answered this question at the 60% level, recognising we may need to update our CSR screening for some ESG issues abd the level of detail that the latter go into.', 'We are in the process of reviewing this area.', 'We formally consider social and environmental issues as part of our bespoke review of individual investments.  There is a question in Endless'' ''Investment Checklist'', that has to be completed on each investment at an early and IC stage, that prompts for confirmation that such issues have been assessed.  Many, if not most, of our investments proceed at a pace that means we do not have time to undertake formal, 3rd party due dilgience on environmental issues, but we do consider them on each investment.', 'As above, we review each company/investment on a bespoke basis, internally by Endless personnel.  We would only engage third party advisers if our review indicated specific reasons to do so on that investment.', 'I am not sure I totally understand the question.  Endless takes into consideration the requirements of our funds in Endless Fund II and III, in terms of investment areas that are disqualified under the Fund documentation.  Over and above this, we do not have additional LP ESG requirements that we document.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Endless does not donate a specific percentage of gains to charitable organisations, but has set up a charitable foundation ''Endless Turnaround Foundation'' to which the organisation contributes and also the Endless team commit time and energy and organises fund raising events which are also for the benefit of the Endless Turnaround Foundation.  The Foundation, in turn, and Endless team members make donations of money and time to various charitable and social causes across the UK.  Further examples can be provided and/or see Endless'' website for details of the Endless Turnaound Foundation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The current Adveq process will deliver this.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'As per the LPA agreement there are a number of industries where we would not invest such as Pornography and Arms Manufacture or trading.  See also question 9 below.', NULL, NULL, 'We do not understand this question.  If it relates to question 9, then Endless will not invest in these areas.', 'Endless'' approach to ESG issues is more generally set out in the Endless website (www.endlessllp.com) under ''Corporate and Social Responsbility''.  We believe this covers many of the areas in both spirit and practice that ''ESG'' seeks to cover.', 'As per ''11, our commitments in this respect are clearly articulated on the Endless website as is Endless'' demonstrable actions to contribute to the wider society (e.g. via the Endless Turnaround Foundation'' and Apprenticeship schemes at a number of Endless'' portfolio companies).', 'The most simple benefit is avoiding investment situations that have risks, from a reputational or other, point of view in the ESG/CSR arena that may impact on investment returns.  Examples on specific investments are given in question 27 below.', 'No one specific person, but a combination of the Portfolio Director, the Chairman and Partners and the Finance Team ensure that Endless is compliant with all key legislation (e.g. Bribery Act, Money Laundering) as well as ensuring there are checklists in place to ensure CSR/ESG assessment takes place on investments.', 'We have a Portfolio Director, James Woolley, who retains an overview of the portfolio from a number of perspectives, including risk management.', 'We do not retain a specific specialist, but may involve one in certain areas at the appropriate time e.g. environment issues relating to the Crown Paints properties when under Endess'' ownership.', 'We do not get this information in a regimented way, but Endless is represented on the Board of each investee company and there will be specific reviews in some of these areas at the company level via Board reports, etc.', 'Not specific one off training in these areas, but there is ''on the job'' training to make sure investment staff are aware of such issues and the checklists in Endless'' investment documentation ensures that such issues are debated at early stage Launchpads and at Investment Committee.', 'Staff are, where relevant, appraised for their portfolio management performance in the generality, which might include portfolio risk issues.', NULL, '¬£45m out of ¬£14m of third party LP investments.', NULL, 'We would consider a request, dependent on the wording and requiremements of such a letter and any impact on Endless'' ability to invest and/or any impact on other investors in Endless'' Funds.  We believe, however, that the nature of Endless'' investment which helps preserve jobs and rescue businesses, combined with our current CSR approach and the overall ethos and culture of the company, helps address any concerns that an investor may have in this area.', 'Via the checklists in our investment processes.', 'The process is driven by havi