(6171, '151', 'G.1.1', 'yes', 'Liberata''s policy and procedure is implemented in accordance with the legislative requirements of the Bribery Act 2010. The Bribery Act 2010 introduces new criminal offences for bribery for both individuals and companies and came into force on 1 July 2011. The Public Interest Disclosure Act 1998 is also relevant and there are other Liberata policies that supplement this policy. These include: Code of Conduct, Whistle blowing Policy and Procedure, Expenses Policy, Client Fraud Policy and Procedure. \r\n', '5.71'),
