(6351, '151', 'S.2.2', 'yes', 'The company has a procurement policy which covers the supply of goods and services. The company uses Safe Contractor, an external organisation, to govern the use of suppliers working at our sites or our Client sites. The SAFEcontractor Scheme is a third party health and safety accreditation system that provides Clients with an auditable trail of evidence, showing that they have undertaken sufficient assessments of the supply chain‚Äôs heath and safety management systems. The Scheme ensures that Clients are complying with Appendix 4 of the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2007 (CDM 2007) and the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2007 by exceeding the requirements of stage 1 core criteria assessments.', '11.00'),
